        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 26 at 3:38PM MDT by NWS Salt Lake City UT</headline>
        <description>At 338 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles northwest of Big Water, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of central Kane
County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
